1981static uint64_t getDwoId(const DWARFDie &CUDie, const DWARFUnit &Unit) {
1982 auto DwoId = dwarf::toUnsigned(
1983 CUDie.find({dwarf::DW_AT_dwo_id, dwarf::DW_AT_GNU_dwo_id}));
1984 if (DwoId)
1985 return *DwoId;
1986 return 0;
1987}
1988
1989static std::string remapPath(StringRef Path,
1990 const objectPrefixMap &ObjectPrefixMap) {
1991 if (ObjectPrefixMap.empty())
1992 return Path.str();
1993
1994 SmallString<256> p = Path;
1995 for (const auto &Entry : ObjectPrefixMap)
1996 if (llvm::sys::path::replace_path_prefix(p, Entry.first, Entry.second))
1997 break;
1998 return p.str().str();
1999}
2000
2001bool DWARFLinker::registerModuleReference(DWARFDie CUDie, const DWARFUnit &Unit,
2002 const DWARFFile &File,
2003 OffsetsStringPool &StringPool,
2004 DeclContextTree &ODRContexts,
2005 uint64_t ModulesEndOffset,
2006 unsigned &UnitID, bool IsLittleEndian,
2007 unsigned Indent, bool Quiet) {
2008 std::string PCMfile = dwarf::toString(
2009 CUDie.find({dwarf::DW_AT_dwo_name, dwarf::DW_AT_GNU_dwo_name}), "");
2010 if (PCMfile.empty())
2011 return false;
2012 if (Options.ObjectPrefixMap)
2013 PCMfile = remapPath(PCMfile, *Options.ObjectPrefixMap);
2014
2015 // Clang module DWARF skeleton CUs abuse this for the path to the module.
2016 uint64_t DwoId = getDwoId(CUDie, Unit);
2017
2018 std::string Name = dwarf::toString(CUDie.find(dwarf::DW_AT_name), "");
2019 if (Name.empty()) {
2020 if (!Quiet)
2021 reportWarning("Anonymous module skeleton CU for " + PCMfile, File);
2022 return true;
2023 }
2024
2025 if (!Quiet && Options.Verbose) {
2026 outs().indent(Indent);
2027 outs() << "Found clang module reference " << PCMfile;
2028 }
2029
2030 auto Cached = ClangModules.find(PCMfile);
2031 if (Cached != ClangModules.end()) {
2032 // FIXME: Until PR27449 (https://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=27449) is
2033 // fixed in clang, only warn about DWO_id mismatches in verbose mode.
2034 // ASTFileSignatures will change randomly when a module is rebuilt.
2035 if (!Quiet && Options.Verbose && (Cached->second != DwoId))
2036 reportWarning(Twine("hash mismatch: this object file was built against a "
2037 "different version of the module ") +
2038 PCMfile,
2039 File);
2040 if (!Quiet && Options.Verbose)
2041 outs() << " [cached].\n";
2042 return true;
2043 }
2044 if (!Quiet && Options.Verbose)
2045 outs() << " ...\n";
2046
2047 // Cyclic dependencies are disallowed by Clang, but we still
2048 // shouldn't run into an infinite loop, so mark it as processed now.
2049 ClangModules.insert({PCMfile, DwoId});
2050
2051 if (Error E = loadClangModule(CUDie, PCMfile, Name, DwoId, File, StringPool,
2052 ODRContexts, ModulesEndOffset, UnitID,
2053 IsLittleEndian, Indent + 2, Quiet)) {
2054 consumeError(std::move(E));
2055 return false;
2056 }
2057 return true;
2058}
2059
2060Error DWARFLinker::loadClangModule(
2061 DWARFDie CUDie, StringRef Filename, StringRef ModuleName, uint64_t DwoId,
2062 const DWARFFile &File, OffsetsStringPool &StringPool,
2063 DeclContextTree &ODRContexts, uint64_t ModulesEndOffset, unsigned &UnitID,
2064 bool IsLittleEndian, unsigned Indent, bool Quiet) {
2065 /// Using a SmallString<0> because loadClangModule() is recursive.
2066 SmallString<0> Path(Options.PrependPath);
2067 if (sys::path::is_relative(Filename))
2068 resolveRelativeObjectPath(Path, CUDie);
2069 sys::path::append(Path, Filename);
2070 // Don't use the cached binary holder because we have no thread-safety
2071 // guarantee and the lifetime is limited.
2072
2073 if (Options.ObjFileLoader == nullptr)
2074 return Error::success();
2075
2076 auto ErrOrObj = Options.ObjFileLoader(File.FileName, Path);
2077 if (!ErrOrObj)
2078 return Error::success();
2079
2080 std::unique_ptr<CompileUnit> Unit;
2081
2082 for (const auto &CU : ErrOrObj->Dwarf->compile_units()) {
2083 updateDwarfVersion(CU->getVersion());
2084 // Recursively get all modules imported by this one.
2085 auto CUDie = CU->getUnitDIE(false);
2086 if (!CUDie)
2087 continue;
2088 if (!registerModuleReference(CUDie, *CU, File, StringPool, ODRContexts,
2089 ModulesEndOffset, UnitID, IsLittleEndian,
2090 Indent, Quiet)) {
2091 if (Unit) {
2092 std::string Err =
2093 (Filename +
2094 ": Clang modules are expected to have exactly 1 compile unit.\n")
2095 .str();
2096 reportError(Err, File);
2097 return make_error<StringError>(Err, inconvertibleErrorCode());
2098 }
2099 // FIXME: Until PR27449 (https://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=27449) is
2100 // fixed in clang, only warn about DWO_id mismatches in verbose mode.
2101 // ASTFileSignatures will change randomly when a module is rebuilt.
2102 uint64_t PCMDwoId = getDwoId(CUDie, *CU);
2103 if (PCMDwoId != DwoId) {
2104 if (!Quiet && Options.Verbose)
2105 reportWarning(
2106 Twine("hash mismatch: this object file was built against a "
2107 "different version of the module ") +
2108 Filename,
2109 File);
2110 // Update the cache entry with the DwoId of the module loaded from disk.
2111 ClangModules[Filename] = PCMDwoId;
2112 }
2113
2114 // Add this module.
2115 Unit = std::make_unique<CompileUnit>(*CU, UnitID++, !Options.NoODR,
2116 ModuleName);
2117 Unit->setHasInterestingContent();
2118 analyzeContextInfo(CUDie, 0, *Unit, &ODRContexts.getRoot(), ODRContexts,
2119 ModulesEndOffset, Options.ParseableSwiftInterfaces,
2120 [&](const Twine &Warning, const DWARFDie &DIE) {
2121 reportWarning(Warning, File, &DIE);
2122 });
2123 // Keep everything.
2124 Unit->markEverythingAsKept();
2125 }
2126 }
2127 if (!Unit->getOrigUnit().getUnitDIE().hasChildren())
2128 return Error::success();
2129 if (!Quiet && Options.Verbose) {
2130 outs().indent(Indent);
2131 outs() << "cloning .debug_info from " << Filename << "\n";
2132 }
2133
2134 UnitListTy CompileUnits;
2135 CompileUnits.push_back(std::move(Unit));
2136 assert(TheDwarfEmitter);
2137 DIECloner(*this, TheDwarfEmitter, *ErrOrObj, DIEAlloc, CompileUnits,
2138 Options.Update)
2139 .cloneAllCompileUnits(*(ErrOrObj->Dwarf), File, StringPool,
2140 IsLittleEndian);
2141 return Error::success();
2142}
2143
2144uint64_t DWARFLinker::DIECloner::cloneAllCompileUnits(
2145 DWARFContext &DwarfContext, const DWARFFile &File,
2146 OffsetsStringPool &StringPool, bool IsLittleEndian) {
2147 uint64_t OutputDebugInfoSize =
2148 Linker.Options.NoOutput ? 0 : Emitter->getDebugInfoSectionSize();
2149 const uint64_t StartOutputDebugInfoSize = OutputDebugInfoSize;
2150
2151 for (auto &CurrentUnit : CompileUnits) {
2152 const uint16_t DwarfVersion = CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit().getVersion();
2153 const uint32_t UnitHeaderSize = DwarfVersion >= 5 ? 12 : 11;
2154 auto InputDIE = CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit().getUnitDIE();
2155 CurrentUnit->setStartOffset(OutputDebugInfoSize);
2156 if (!InputDIE) {
2157 OutputDebugInfoSize = CurrentUnit->computeNextUnitOffset(DwarfVersion);
2158 continue;
2159 }
2160 if (CurrentUnit->getInfo(0).Keep) {
2161 // Clone the InputDIE into your Unit DIE in our compile unit since it
2162 // already has a DIE inside of it.
2163 CurrentUnit->createOutputDIE();
2164 cloneDIE(InputDIE, File, *CurrentUnit, StringPool, 0 /* PC offset */,
2165 UnitHeaderSize, 0, IsLittleEndian,
2166 CurrentUnit->getOutputUnitDIE());
2167 }
2168
2169 OutputDebugInfoSize = CurrentUnit->computeNextUnitOffset(DwarfVersion);
2170
2171 if (!Linker.Options.NoOutput) {
2172 assert(Emitter);
2173
2174 if (LLVM_LIKELY(!Linker.Options.Update) ||
2175 Linker.needToTranslateStrings())
2176 Linker.patchLineTableForUnit(*CurrentUnit, DwarfContext, File);
2177
2178 Linker.emitAcceleratorEntriesForUnit(*CurrentUnit);
2179
2180 if (LLVM_UNLIKELY(Linker.Options.Update))
2181 continue;
2182
2183 Linker.patchRangesForUnit(*CurrentUnit, DwarfContext, File);
2184 auto ProcessExpr = [&](StringRef Bytes,
2185 SmallVectorImpl<uint8_t> &Buffer) {
2186 DWARFUnit &OrigUnit = CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit();
2187 DataExtractor Data(Bytes, IsLittleEndian,
2188 OrigUnit.getAddressByteSize());
2189 cloneExpression(Data,
2190 DWARFExpression(Data, OrigUnit.getAddressByteSize(),
2191 OrigUnit.getFormParams().Format),
2192 File, *CurrentUnit, Buffer);
2193 };
2194 Emitter->emitLocationsForUnit(*CurrentUnit, DwarfContext, ProcessExpr);
2195 }
2196 }
2197
2198 if (!Linker.Options.NoOutput) {
2199 assert(Emitter);
2200 // Emit all the compile unit's debug information.
2201 for (auto &CurrentUnit : CompileUnits) {
2202 if (LLVM_LIKELY(!Linker.Options.Update))
2203 Linker.generateUnitRanges(*CurrentUnit);
2204
2205 CurrentUnit->fixupForwardReferences();
2206
2207 if (!CurrentUnit->getOutputUnitDIE())
2208 continue;
2209
2210 unsigned DwarfVersion = CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit().getVersion();
2211
2212 assert(Emitter->getDebugInfoSectionSize() ==
2213 CurrentUnit->getStartOffset());
2214 Emitter->emitCompileUnitHeader(*CurrentUnit, DwarfVersion);
2215 Emitter->emitDIE(*CurrentUnit->getOutputUnitDIE());
2216 assert(Emitter->getDebugInfoSectionSize() ==
2217 CurrentUnit->computeNextUnitOffset(DwarfVersion));
2218 }
2219 }
2220
2221 return OutputDebugInfoSize - StartOutputDebugInfoSize;
2222}

2224void DWARFLinker::updateAccelKind(DWARFContext &Dwarf) {
2225 if (Options.TheAccelTableKind != AccelTableKind::Default)
2226 return;
2227
2228 auto &DwarfObj = Dwarf.getDWARFObj();
2229
2230 if (!AtLeastOneDwarfAccelTable &&

2233 !DwarfObj.getAppleNamespacesSection().Data.empty() ||
2234 !DwarfObj.getAppleObjCSection().Data.empty())) {
2235 AtLeastOneAppleAccelTable = true;

2239 AtLeastOneDwarfAccelTable = true;
2240 }

2243bool DWARFLinker::emitPaperTrailWarnings(const DWARFFile &File,
2244 OffsetsStringPool &StringPool) {
2245
2246 if (File.Warnings.empty())
2247 return false;
2248
2249 DIE *CUDie = DIE::get(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_TAG_compile_unit);
2250 CUDie->setOffset(11);
2251 StringRef Producer;
2252 StringRef WarningHeader;
2253
2254 switch (DwarfLinkerClientID) {
2255 case DwarfLinkerClient::Dsymutil:
2256 Producer = StringPool.internString("dsymutil");
2257 WarningHeader = "dsymutil_warning";
2258 break;
2259
2260 default:
2261 Producer = StringPool.internString("dwarfopt");
2262 WarningHeader = "dwarfopt_warning";
2263 break;
2264 }
2265
2266 StringRef FileName = StringPool.internString(File.FileName);
2267 CUDie->addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_AT_producer, dwarf::DW_FORM_strp,
2268 DIEInteger(StringPool.getStringOffset(Producer)));
2269 DIEBlock *String = new (DIEAlloc) DIEBlock();
2270 DIEBlocks.push_back(String);
2271 for (auto &C : FileName)
2272 String->addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::Attribute(0), dwarf::DW_FORM_data1,
2273 DIEInteger(C));
2274 String->addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::Attribute(0), dwarf::DW_FORM_data1,
2275 DIEInteger(0));
2276
2277 CUDie->addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_AT_name, dwarf::DW_FORM_string, String);
2278 for (const auto &Warning : File.Warnings) {
2279 DIE &ConstDie = CUDie->addChild(DIE::get(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_TAG_constant));
2280 ConstDie.addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_AT_name, dwarf::DW_FORM_strp,
2281 DIEInteger(StringPool.getStringOffset(WarningHeader)));
2282 ConstDie.addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_AT_artificial, dwarf::DW_FORM_flag,
2283 DIEInteger(1));
2284 ConstDie.addValue(DIEAlloc, dwarf::DW_AT_const_value, dwarf::DW_FORM_strp,
2285 DIEInteger(StringPool.getStringOffset(Warning)));
2286 }
2287 unsigned Size = 4 /* FORM_strp */ + FileName.size() + 1 +
2288 File.Warnings.size() * (4 + 1 + 4) + 1 /* End of children */;
2289 DIEAbbrev Abbrev = CUDie->generateAbbrev();
2290 assignAbbrev(Abbrev);
2291 CUDie->setAbbrevNumber(Abbrev.getNumber());
2292 Size += getULEB128Size(Abbrev.getNumber());
2293 // Abbreviation ordering needed for classic compatibility.
2294 for (auto &Child : CUDie->children()) {
2295 Abbrev = Child.generateAbbrev();
2296 assignAbbrev(Abbrev);
2297 Child.setAbbrevNumber(Abbrev.getNumber());
2298 Size += getULEB128Size(Abbrev.getNumber());
2299 }
2300 CUDie->setSize(Size);
2301 TheDwarfEmitter->emitPaperTrailWarningsDie(*CUDie);
2302
2303 return true;
2304}

2326
2327bool DWARFLinker::link() {
2328 assert(Options.NoOutput || TheDwarfEmitter);
2329
2330 // A unique ID that identifies each compile unit.
2331 unsigned UnitID = 0;
2332
2333 // First populate the data structure we need for each iteration of the
2334 // parallel loop.
2335 unsigned NumObjects = ObjectContexts.size();
2336
2337 // This Dwarf string pool which is used for emission. It must be used
2338 // serially as the order of calling getStringOffset matters for
2339 // reproducibility.
2340 OffsetsStringPool OffsetsStringPool(StringsTranslator, true);
2341
2342 // ODR Contexts for the optimize.
2343 DeclContextTree ODRContexts;
2344
2345 // If we haven't decided on an accelerator table kind yet, we base ourselves
2346 // on the DWARF we have seen so far. At this point we haven't pulled in debug
2347 // information from modules yet, so it is technically possible that they
2348 // would affect the decision. However, as they're built with the same
2349 // compiler and flags, it is safe to assume that they will follow the
2350 // decision made here.
2351 if (Options.TheAccelTableKind == AccelTableKind::Default) {
2352 if (AtLeastOneDwarfAccelTable && !AtLeastOneAppleAccelTable)
2353 Options.TheAccelTableKind = AccelTableKind::Dwarf;
2354 else
2355 Options.TheAccelTableKind = AccelTableKind::Apple;
2356 }
2357
2358 for (LinkContext &OptContext : ObjectContexts) {
2359 if (Options.Verbose) {
2360 if (DwarfLinkerClientID == DwarfLinkerClient::Dsymutil)
2361 outs() << "DEBUG MAP OBJECT: " << OptContext.File.FileName << "\n";
2362 else
2363 outs() << "OBJECT FILE: " << OptContext.File.FileName << "\n";
2364 }
2365
2366 if (emitPaperTrailWarnings(OptContext.File, OffsetsStringPool))
2367 continue;
2368
2369 if (!OptContext.File.Dwarf)
2370 continue;
2371 // Look for relocations that correspond to address map entries.
2372
2373 // there was findvalidrelocations previously ... probably we need to gather
2374 // info here
2375 if (LLVM_LIKELY(!Options.Update) &&
2376 !OptContext.File.Addresses->hasValidRelocs()) {
2377 if (Options.Verbose)
2378 outs() << "No valid relocations found. Skipping.\n";
2379
2380 // Set "Skip" flag as a signal to other loops that we should not
2381 // process this iteration.
2382 OptContext.Skip = true;
2383 continue;
2384 }
2385
2386 // Setup access to the debug info.
2387 if (!OptContext.File.Dwarf)
2388 continue;
2389
2390 // In a first phase, just read in the debug info and load all clang modules.
2391 OptContext.CompileUnits.reserve(
2392 OptContext.File.Dwarf->getNumCompileUnits());
2393
2394 for (const auto &CU : OptContext.File.Dwarf->compile_units()) {
2395 updateDwarfVersion(CU->getVersion());
2396 auto CUDie = CU->getUnitDIE(false);
2397 if (Options.Verbose) {
2398 outs() << "Input compilation unit:";
2399 DIDumpOptions DumpOpts;
2400 DumpOpts.ChildRecurseDepth = 0;
2401 DumpOpts.Verbose = Options.Verbose;
2402 CUDie.dump(outs(), 0, DumpOpts);
2403 }
2404 if (CUDie && !LLVM_UNLIKELY(Options.Update))
2405 registerModuleReference(CUDie, *CU, OptContext.File, OffsetsStringPool,
2406 ODRContexts, 0, UnitID,
2407 OptContext.File.Dwarf->isLittleEndian());
2408 }
2409 }
2410
2411 // If we haven't seen any CUs, pick an arbitrary valid Dwarf version anyway.
2412 if (MaxDwarfVersion == 0)
2413 MaxDwarfVersion = 3;
2414
2415 // At this point we know how much data we have emitted. We use this value to
2416 // compare canonical DIE offsets in analyzeContextInfo to see if a definition
2417 // is already emitted, without being affected by canonical die offsets set
2418 // later. This prevents undeterminism when analyze and clone execute
2419 // concurrently, as clone set the canonical DIE offset and analyze reads it.
2420 const uint64_t ModulesEndOffset =
2421 Options.NoOutput ? 0 : TheDwarfEmitter->getDebugInfoSectionSize();
2422
2423 // These variables manage the list of processed object files.
2424 // The mutex and condition variable are to ensure that this is thread safe.
2425 std::mutex ProcessedFilesMutex;
2426 std::condition_variable ProcessedFilesConditionVariable;
2427 BitVector ProcessedFiles(NumObjects, false);
2428
2429 // Analyzing the context info is particularly expensive so it is executed in
2430 // parallel with emitting the previous compile unit.
2431 auto AnalyzeLambda = [&](size_t I) {
2432 auto &Context = ObjectContexts[I];
2433
2434 if (Context.Skip || !Context.File.Dwarf)
2435 return;
2436
2437 for (const auto &CU : Context.File.Dwarf->compile_units()) {
2438 updateDwarfVersion(CU->getVersion());
2439 // The !registerModuleReference() condition effectively skips
2440 // over fully resolved skeleton units. This second pass of
2441 // registerModuleReferences doesn't do any new work, but it
2442 // will collect top-level errors, which are suppressed. Module
2443 // warnings were already displayed in the first iteration.
2444 bool Quiet = true;
2445 auto CUDie = CU->getUnitDIE(false);
2446 if (!CUDie || LLVM_UNLIKELY(Options.Update) ||
2447 !registerModuleReference(CUDie, *CU, Context.File, OffsetsStringPool,
2448 ODRContexts, ModulesEndOffset, UnitID,
2449 Quiet)) {
2450 Context.CompileUnits.push_back(std::make_unique<CompileUnit>(
2451 *CU, UnitID++, !Options.NoODR && !Options.Update, ""));
2452 }
2453 }
2454
2455 // Now build the DIE parent links that we will use during the next phase.
2456 for (auto &CurrentUnit : Context.CompileUnits) {
2457 auto CUDie = CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit().getUnitDIE();
2458 if (!CUDie)
2459 continue;
2460 analyzeContextInfo(CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit().getUnitDIE(), 0,
2461 *CurrentUnit, &ODRContexts.getRoot(), ODRContexts,
2462 ModulesEndOffset, Options.ParseableSwiftInterfaces,
2463 [&](const Twine &Warning, const DWARFDie &DIE) {
2464 reportWarning(Warning, Context.File, &DIE);
2465 });
2466 }
2467 };
2468
2469 // For each object file map how many bytes were emitted.
2470 StringMap<DebugInfoSize> SizeByObject;
2471
2472 // And then the remaining work in serial again.
2473 // Note, although this loop runs in serial, it can run in parallel with
2474 // the analyzeContextInfo loop so long as we process files with indices >=
2475 // than those processed by analyzeContextInfo.
2476 auto CloneLambda = [&](size_t I) {
2477 auto &OptContext = ObjectContexts[I];
2478 if (OptContext.Skip || !OptContext.File.Dwarf)
2479 return;
2480
2481 // Then mark all the DIEs that need to be present in the generated output
2482 // and collect some information about them.
2483 // Note that this loop can not be merged with the previous one because
2484 // cross-cu references require the ParentIdx to be setup for every CU in
2485 // the object file before calling this.
2486 if (LLVM_UNLIKELY(Options.Update)) {
2487 for (auto &CurrentUnit : OptContext.CompileUnits)
2488 CurrentUnit->markEverythingAsKept();
2489 copyInvariantDebugSection(*OptContext.File.Dwarf);
2490 } else {
2491 for (auto &CurrentUnit : OptContext.CompileUnits)
2492 lookForDIEsToKeep(*OptContext.File.Addresses,
2493 OptContext.File.Addresses->getValidAddressRanges(),
2494 OptContext.CompileUnits,
2495 CurrentUnit->getOrigUnit().getUnitDIE(),
2496 OptContext.File, *CurrentUnit, 0);
2497 }
2498
2499 // The calls to applyValidRelocs inside cloneDIE will walk the reloc
2500 // array again (in the same way findValidRelocsInDebugInfo() did). We
2501 // need to reset the NextValidReloc index to the beginning.
2502 if (OptContext.File.Addresses->hasValidRelocs() ||
2503 LLVM_UNLIKELY(Options.Update)) {
2504 SizeByObject[OptContext.File.FileName].Input =
2505 getDebugInfoSize(*OptContext.File.Dwarf);
2506 SizeByObject[OptContext.File.FileName].Output =
2507 DIECloner(*this, TheDwarfEmitter, OptContext.File, DIEAlloc,
2508 OptContext.CompileUnits, Options.Update)
2509 .cloneAllCompileUnits(*OptContext.File.Dwarf, OptContext.File,
2510 OffsetsStringPool,
2511 OptContext.File.Dwarf->isLittleEndian());
2512 }
2513 if (!Options.NoOutput && !OptContext.CompileUnits.empty() &&
2514 LLVM_LIKELY(!Options.Update))
2515 patchFrameInfoForObject(
2516 OptContext.File, OptContext.File.Addresses->getValidAddressRanges(),
2517 *OptContext.File.Dwarf,
2518 OptContext.CompileUnits[0]->getOrigUnit().getAddressByteSize());
2519
2520 // Clean-up before starting working on the next object.
2521 cleanupAuxiliarryData(OptContext);
2522 };
2523
2524 auto EmitLambda = [&]() {
2525 // Emit everything that's global.
2526 if (!Options.NoOutput) {
2527 TheDwarfEmitter->emitAbbrevs(Abbreviations, MaxDwarfVersion);
2528 TheDwarfEmitter->emitStrings(OffsetsStringPool);
2529 switch (Options.TheAccelTableKind) {
2530 case AccelTableKind::Apple:
2531 TheDwarfEmitter->emitAppleNames(AppleNames);
2532 TheDwarfEmitter->emitAppleNamespaces(AppleNamespaces);
2533 TheDwarfEmitter->emitAppleTypes(AppleTypes);
2534 TheDwarfEmitter->emitAppleObjc(AppleObjc);
2535 break;
2536 case AccelTableKind::Dwarf:
2537 TheDwarfEmitter->emitDebugNames(DebugNames);
2538 break;
2539 case AccelTableKind::Default:
2540 llvm_unreachable("Default should have already been resolved.");
2541 break;
2542 }
2543 }
2544 };
2545
2546 auto AnalyzeAll = [&]() {
2547 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NumObjects; I != E; ++I) {
2548 AnalyzeLambda(I);
2549
2550 std::unique_lock<std::mutex> LockGuard(ProcessedFilesMutex);
2551 ProcessedFiles.set(I);
2552 ProcessedFilesConditionVariable.notify_one();
2553 }
2554 };
2555
2556 auto CloneAll = [&]() {
2557 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NumObjects; I != E; ++I) {
2558 {
2559 std::unique_lock<std::mutex> LockGuard(ProcessedFilesMutex);
2560 if (!ProcessedFiles[I]) {
2561 ProcessedFilesConditionVariable.wait(
2562 LockGuard, [&]() { return ProcessedFiles[I]; });
2563 }
2564 }
2565
2566 CloneLambda(I);
2567 }
2568 EmitLambda();
2569 };
2570
2571 // To limit memory usage in the single threaded case, analyze and clone are
2572 // run sequentially so the OptContext is freed after processing each object
2573 // in endDebugObject.
2574 if (Options.Threads == 1) {
2575 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NumObjects; I != E; ++I) {
2576 AnalyzeLambda(I);
2577 CloneLambda(I);
2578 }
2579 EmitLambda();
2580 } else {
2581 ThreadPool Pool(hardware_concurrency(2));
2582 Pool.async(AnalyzeAll);
2583 Pool.async(CloneAll);
2584 Pool.wait();
2585 }
2586
2587 if (Options.Statistics) {
2588 // Create a vector sorted in descending order by output size.
2589 std::vector<std::pair<StringRef, DebugInfoSize>> Sorted;
2590 for (auto &E : SizeByObject)
2591 Sorted.emplace_back(E.first(), E.second);
2592 llvm::sort(Sorted, [](auto &LHS, auto &RHS) {
2593 return LHS.second.Output > RHS.second.Output;
2594 });
2595
2596 auto ComputePercentange = [](int64_t Input, int64_t Output) -> float {
2597 const float Difference = Output - Input;
2598 const float Sum = Input + Output;
2599 if (Sum == 0)
2600 return 0;
2601 return (Difference / (Sum / 2));
2602 };
2603
2604 int64_t InputTotal = 0;
2605 int64_t OutputTotal = 0;
2606 const char *FormatStr = "{0,-45} {1,10}b {2,10}b {3,8:P}\n";
2607
2608 // Print header.
2609 outs() << ".debug_info section size (in bytes)\n";
2610 outs() << "----------------------------------------------------------------"
2611 "---------------\n";
2612 outs() << "Filename Object "
2613 " dSYM Change\n";
2614 outs() << "----------------------------------------------------------------"
2615 "---------------\n";
2616
2617 // Print body.
2618 for (auto &E : Sorted) {
2619 InputTotal += E.second.Input;
2620 OutputTotal += E.second.Output;
2621 llvm::outs() << formatv(
2622 FormatStr, sys::path::filename(E.first).take_back(45), E.second.Input,
2623 E.second.Output, ComputePercentange(E.second.Input, E.second.Output));
2624 }
2625 // Print total and footer.
2626 outs() << "----------------------------------------------------------------"
2627 "---------------\n";
2628 llvm::outs() << formatv(FormatStr, "Total", InputTotal, OutputTotal,
2629 ComputePercentange(InputTotal, OutputTotal));
2630 outs() << "----------------------------------------------------------------"
2631 "---------------\n\n";
2632 }
2633
2634 return true;
2635}
